g%20manager%20going%20through%20papers%20without%20actually%20knowing%20you.%20While%20cold-applying%20isn't%20the%20most%20effective%2C%20if%20you%20have%20a%20strong%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%2C%20it%20can%20eventually%20work%20out%20for%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-pay-guidelines-new-hire-offers-exception-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esoftware%20engineers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20at%20least%20from%20what%20I've%20seen%20throughout%20my%20career%2C%20the%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20is%20definitely%20the%20most%20important%20thing.%20The%20cover%20letter%20is%20almost%20always%20optional.%20So%20I%20took%20extra%20care%20to%20make%20my%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20stand%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22be38ad5f-686e-49d2-a03f-628ab36af7e1%5C%22%3EHighlight%20your%20individual%20projects%2C%20including%20ones%20you%20did%20on%20the%20side%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20have%20any%20internship%20experiences%20or%20previous%20work%20experience%2C%20that%20should%20be%20something%20that%20you%20highlight%20at%20the%20top%20of%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20because%20that%20immediately%20makes%20it%20stand%20out%2C%20even%20if%20it%20was%20just%20three%20or%20four%20months.%20Some%20companies%20also%20take%20co-ops%2C%20and%20I%20was%20a%20co-op%20intern%20at%20a%20startup%20for%20seven%20months.%20That%20was%20at%20the%20top%20of%20my%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20also%20should%20list%20individual%20projects%20you%20have%20worked%20on.%20For%20every%20project%20that%20I%20had%20listed%20on%20my%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%2C%20I%20made%20sure%20to%20highlight%20the%20programming%20languages%20and%20tools%20and%20how%20I%20used%20them.%20This%20helps%20in%20two%20ways.%20It%20helps%20somebody%20reading%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20understand%20that%20you%20have%20this%20breadth%20of%20tools%20and%20languages%20that%20you%20have%20used%2C%20and%20then%2C%20within%20the%20project%20description%2C%20you%20go%20into%20two%20to%20three%20lines%20of%20detail%20to%20explain%20how%20you%20used%20those%20particular%20tools.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20should%20have%20three%20kinds%20of%20projects%3A%20One%20would%20be%20a%20project%20you%20worked%20on%20in%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-turn-summer-internship-into-full-time-job-offer-steps-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Einternship%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Another%20is%20going%20to%20be%20the%20projects%20that%20you%20did%20as%20part%20of%20your%20coursework%2C%20in%20grad%20school%20or%20undergrad.%20And%20then%20the%20third%20should%20be%20all%20the%20extra%20projects%20that%20you%20did%20on%20the%20side%2C%20which%20show%20that%20you're%20really%20passionate%20about%20becoming%20a%20software%20engineer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20would%20be%20something%20you%20did%20on%20your%20own%20time.%20Nobody%20gave%20you%20grades%2C%20and%20you%20didn't%20have%20to%20submit%20this%20at%20a%20particular%20time.%20No%20deadlines%2C%20no%20assessment.%20Just%20something%20that%20you%20did%20for%20yourself.%20One%20of%20these%20I%20included%20was%20a%20Facebook%20chatbot%20I%20made%2C%20which%20you%20could%20use%20to%20get%20information%20about%20books.%20So%20you%20would%20essentially%20be%20talking%20to%20a%20chatbot%20and%20asking%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20about%20this%20book%3F%26quot%3B%20And%20it%20would%20give%20you%20a%20quick%20summary.%20I%20built%20it%20using%20publicly%20available%20APIs%20from%20GoodReads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a0ebbaa7-9b54-4f96-9e67-e597d1a7df8a%5C%22%3EShow%20your%20work%20with%20GitHub%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20software%20engineers%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgithub%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGitHub%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20like%20a%20substitute%20for%20a%20cover%20letter.%20It's%20something%20that%20everybody%20uses%20to%20maintain%20their%20code%20in%2C%20and%20you%20can%20have%20a%20private%20repository%2C%20or%20you%20can%20have%20a%20public%20repository.%20I%20leveraged%20it%20by%20keeping%20all%20the%20projects%20that%20I%20did%20as%20part%20of%20my%20coursework%20updated%20in%20my%20GitHub%20profile.%20I%20also%20made%20sure%20that%20I%20updated%20the%20code%20for%20all%20these%20tiny%20extracurricular%20projects%20that%20I%20had.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20I%20put%20my%20GitHub%20username%20on%20the%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20itself%20and%20hyperlinked%20to%20my%20actual%20GitHub%20portfolio%20page.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20way%2C%20if%20a%20prospective%20hiring%20manager%20is%20going%20through%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%2C%20and%20let's%20say%20one%20of%20your%20projects%20catches%20their%20eye%20%E2%80%94%20if%20they%20want%20to%20go%20look%20at%20it%2C%20you%20are%20giving%20free%20and%20easy%20access%20to%20them%20right%20there.%20That%20automatically%20gives%20you%20an%20edge%20over%20somebody%20else%20who's%20just%20written%2C%20%26quot%3Bworked%20on%20this%20chatbot%20for%20X%20and%20Y.%26quot%3B%20Having%20the%20code%20out%20there%20in%20GitHub%20shows%20this%20website%20was%20actually%20coded%20by%20you%2C%20and%20you%20didn't%20use%20a%20website%20builder%20tool.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20allows%20your%20work%20to%20speak%20for%20itself.%20It's%20not%20like%20you've%20just%20written%20down%20something%20on%20a%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9.%20When%20you%20put%20it%20out%20there%20on%20GitHub%2C%20it%20proves%20that%20you've%20actually%20done%20something%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20all%20these%20AI%20tools%20and%20AI%20agents%20now%20that%20can%20make%20your%20life%20a%20little%20easier%2C%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvibe-coding-ai-silicon-valley-andrej-karpathy-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Evibe%20coding%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20definitely%20a%20phenomenon.%20But%20before%20you%20jump%20into%20that%2C%20it's%20always%20better%20to%20have%20a%20deeper%20understanding%20of%20the%20code%20that%20you're%20working%20with%20because%20there%20is%20only%20so%20much